@help HELP

@node MAIN "Ermmm... Is anyone reading this?"

Do You like OS3.5+ icons? You do not own OS3.5 package? Is it hopeless?
The answer is simple: NO ;)

This small utility does convert OS3.5+ PaletteMapped icons into NewIcons.
Whole hard job is made by ConvertColorIcon. All You have to do is specify some
arguments. Not too hard isn't it? ;)

 @{" Installation " link INSTALL}
 @{" Requirements " link REQ}
 @{" Features " link FEATURES}
 @{" Usage " link USAGE}
 @{" BUGS " link BUGS}
 @{" History " link HISTORY}
 @{" Credits " link CREDITS}
 @{" Author " link AUTHOR}

Latest news:
I've made a small hack - ConvColorIconR which can recurse into directories and subdirectories and so on..
Be warned, it's a quick'n'dirty hack. Use at your ow risk.

Sad (i hope so;) news...
I've decided to relase source of than simple program as I don't have much time to keep developing it. Also
i've sold my miggy. I've tried UAE, but it's not the same.
I did rewrite whole program from scratch and achieved first goal - /M support. But there are still things
to do such as:
 -less questions when converting whole drawers
 -colorise errors & notices
 -quiet mode
 -reimplement tooltypes
 -localisation (.cd file already created)
 -convert drawers recursively (sample source included)

I've included source codes written in AmigaE for both ConvertColorIcon and YAIPT. Also I've included special
edition of Convert53Icon (ought to be eXec exclusive, polish only).
If somebody wants to take over developement - feel free. Just notice me about it, please.

@endnode
 
@node INSTALL "How to install?"
 Installation:
 Just copy specified executable (ConvertColorIcon) wherever you want.
 OS3.1 users need to do @{"this" link OS31}.


@endnode
@node REQ "Is Pegasos needed?"

Requirements:
-OS3.5+ to make it fully functional
-OS3.1 to run... Read about it @{"here" link OS31}
-newicon.library V40+ (The original one from newicon package. The OS3.5 patched one does @{b}NOT@{ub} work.)
-asl.library V40+

@endnode
@node FEATURES "Does it play Chess?"

Features:
-long names support (up to 103 characters)
-can convert whole drawers
-simple usage (CLI,WB)
-automagically create shadow for one-image icons


@endnode
@node USAGE "Say HELLO"

Usage:

From CLI:
ICON/A/M:
	Source icons (PaletteMapped)
V=VERBOSE/S:
	Be talkative.

Note:
1. You may specify source with or without '@{b}.info@{ub}' extension.

From Workbench:
Just doubleclick ConvertColorIcon and a Asl Filerequester will popup.
Or drop'n'drop some icons on it.

@endnode
@node BUGS "Is Articia patched? ;)"

BUGS:
Sometimes it crashes when there's to many icons in one directory. Dunno why (doesn't happen here)

LIMITATIONS:
Less features than previous relase (Convert35Icon)
Does not allow to convert icons bigger that 93x93 (NewIcons spec.)

@endnode
@node OS31 "ColorMapped on OS3.1? Naaa ;)"

ConvertColorIcon and OS3.1 Notes:
So You want to convert OS3.5+ icons to NewIcons and You do NOT have OS3.5+ installed?
Yes? So read on...

You have do it manually:

 First You @{b}need @{ub}to get @{i}icon.library@{ui} V44+ and patch it using special
 utility (source included).

 'YAIPT RAM:icon.library'

 It will create c35i.library in RAM:. Copy it to your LIBS: directory.

Done!

Now You may convert any OS3.5+ icon to NewIcon without installed OS3.5...

NOTE: It does NOT work on OS3.0.

@endnode
@node HAND "Let's rock"

 

@endnode



